{"title_page": "Carl Binder", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian television writer and producer|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{notability|Biographies|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Carl Binder\n| image       = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1960|08|10|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Windsor, Ontario]], Canada \n| nationality = \n| other_names = \n| education   = \n| occupation  = [[Screenwriter]]<br/>[[Television Producer]]\n| religion    = \n| spouse      = \n| partner     = \n| children    = \n| parents     = \n| relatives   = \n| website     = \n}}\n'''Carl Binder''' is a Canadian [[television writer]] and [[television producer|producer]]. He is most noted for his contributions to the ''[[Stargate SG-1]]'' and ''[[Stargate Atlantis]]'' series as well as ''[[Dr. Quinn, Medicine Woman]]'' and ''[[Little Men (TV series)|Little Men]]''.\n\nBinder currently resides in [[Vancouver]], [[British Columbia]].\n\n==Career==\nBinder, who hails from [[Ontario]], has worked extensively in television since the mid 1980s. He helped write the 1995 Disney animated movie, ''[[Pocahontas (1995 film)|Pocahontas]]''.<ref>http://www.tv.com/carl-binder/person/38983/summary.html TV</ref> Binder was set to co-write the third ''Stargate SG-1'' movie with [[Brad Wright]] and served as an executive producer for the ''[[Stargate]]'' series ''[[Stargate Universe]]''.<ref>http://www.gateworld.net/news/2009/04/third-sg-1-movie-has-a-go/</ref> More recently, he worked on ''[[Transporter: The Series]]'', ''[[Houdini and Doyle]]'' and the miniseries ''Unspeakable''.\n\n===Trivia===\nIn the ''Stargate Atlantis'' episode 5x16, a hall in a secret scientific facility was called \"Carl Binder Memorial Theater\".\n\n==List of Stargate episodes written by Binder==\n\n===''Stargate SG-1''===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Title\n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Season\n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Notes \n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Directed by \n|- style=\"background-color: #F2F2F2;\" |\n|- style=\"background-color: #F2F2F2;\" |\n| \"[[Demons (Stargate SG-1)|Demons]]\" || 3 || None || Peter DeLuise \n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[200 (Stargate SG-1)|200]]\" || 10 || Written with Brad Wright & Robert C. Cooper & Joseph Mallozzi & Paul Mullie & Martin Gero & Alan McCullough || Martin Wood \n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n|}\n\n===''Stargate Atlantis''===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Title\n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Season\n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Notes \n! style=\"background-color: #DEDDE2\" | Directed by \n|- style=\"background-color: #F2F2F2;\" |\n|- style=\"background-color: #F2F2F2;\" |\n| \"[[Stargate Atlantis (season 1)|Before I Sleep]]\" || 1 || None || Andy Mikita  \n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[Letters From Pegasus]]\" || 1 || None || Mario Azzopardi  \n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[Condemned (Stargate Atlantis)|Condemned]]\" || 2 || Teleplay (Story by Sean Carley) || Peter DeLuise \n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[Aurora (Stargate Atlantis)|Aurora]]\" || 2 || Teleplay (Story by Binder & Brad Wright) || Martin Wood\n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[The Hive (Stargate Atlantis)|The Hive]]\" || 2 || None || Martin Wood\n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[Critical Mass (Stargate Atlantis)|Critical Mass]]\" || 2 || Teleplay (Story by Binder & Brad Wright) || Andy Mikita \n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[Michael (Stargate Atlantis)|Michael]]\" || 2 || None || Martin Wood\n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[Inferno (Stargate Atlantis)|Inferno]]\" || 2 || None || Peter DeLuise \n|- style=\"background-color: #FFFFFF;\" |\n| \"[[Irresistible (Stargate Atlantis)|Irresistible]]\" || 3 || Teleplay (Story by Brad Wright & Robert C. Cooper)