= \n| socks3             = \n| prevseason         = [[1981\u201382 Aberdeen F.C. season|1981\u201382]]\n| nextseason         = [[1983\u201384 Aberdeen F.C. season|1983\u201384]]\n}}\n'''Aberdeen F.C.''' competed in the [[Scottish Premier Division]], [[Scottish Cup]], [[League Cup]] and [[UEFA Cup Winners' Cup|European Cup Winners' Cup]] in [[1982\u201383 in Scottish football|season 1982\u201383]]. They finished third in the Premier Division behind champions [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] and runners-up [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]. In the cups, they retained the Scottish Cup and won the European Cup Winners' Cup with a 2\u20131 win over [[Real Madrid C.F.|Real Madrid]] in Gothenburg.\n\n==Results==\n\n===Friendlies===\n\nIn late July/early August 1982, Aberdeen played three games against [[Highland Football League|Highland League]] opposition. On 7 August, English club Ipswich Town provided the opposition for [[Drew Jarvie]]'s testimonial game, which the English League Division 1 club won 1-0.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Date\n! Opponent\n! H/A\n! Score\n! Aberdeen Scorer(s)\n! Attendance\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|align=left|31 July\n|align=left|[[Ross County F.C.|Ross County]]\n|[[Victoria Park, Dingwall|A]]\n|5\u20130\n|align=left|[[John McMaster (footballer, born 1955)|McMaster]] (2), [[Andy Harrow|Harrow]] (30, 34), [[Eric Black|Black]], (50, 53)\n|0\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|align=left|2 August\n|align=left|[[Nairn County F.C.|Nairn County]]\n|[[Station Park, Nairn|A]]\n|5\u20130\n|align=left|[[Andy Harrow|Harrow]] (4, 22), [[Alex McLeish|McLeish]] (30), [[Mark McGhee|McGhee]] (41), [[Walker McCall|McCall]] (81)\n|1,006\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|align=left|3 August\n|align=left|[[Inverness Thistle F.C.|Inverness Thistle]]\n|[[Kingsmills Park|A]]\n|4\u20130\n|align=left|[[Eric Black|Black]] (16), [[Gordon Strachan|Strachan]] (84 [[Penalty kick (association football)|pen.]], 86, 90)\n|2,500\n|-bgcolor=#FFCCCC\n|align=left|7 August\n|align=left|{{flagicon|ENG}} [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]]\n|[[Pittodrie Stadium|H]]\n|0\u20131\n|align=left|\n|8,200\n|-\n|}\n\n===Scottish Premier Division===\n{{main|1982\u201383 Scottish Premier Division}}\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! Match Day\n! Date\n! Opponent\n! H/A\n! Score\n! Aberdeen Scorer(s)\n! Attendance\n|-bgcolor=#FFCCCC\n|1.\n|align=left|4 September\n|align=left|[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n|[[Tannadice Stadium|A]]\n|0\u20132\n|\n|11,683\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|2.\n|align=left|11 September\n|align=left|[[Greenock Morton F.C.|Morton]]\n|[[Pittodrie Stadium|H]]\n|4\u20131\n|align=left|[[Gordon Strachan|Strachan]] (15 ([[Penalty kick (association football)|pen.]]), [[Eric Black|Black]] (42), [[Neil Simpson|Simpson]] (55), [[John Hewitt (footballer)|Hewitt]] (77) \n|7,500\n|-bgcolor=#FFFFDD\n|3.\n|align=left|18 September\n|align=left|[[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]]\n|[[Love Street|A]]\n|1\u20131\n|align=left|[[Mark McGhee|McGhee]] (64)\n|4,800\n|-bgcolor=#FFCCCC\n|4.\n|align=left|25 September\n|align=left|[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]\n|[[Pittodrie Stadium|H]]\n|1\u20132\n|align=left|[[Gordon Strachan|Strachan]] (73 [[Penalty kick (association football)|pen.]])\n|20,300\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|5.\n|align=left|2 October\n|align=left|[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]\n|[[Pittodrie Stadium|H]]\n|2\u20131\n|align=left|[[Steve Cowan|Cowan]] (66), [[Willie Miller|Miller]] (89)\n|9,000\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|6.\n|align=left|9 October\n|align=left|[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]\n|[[Celtic Park|A]]\n|3\u20131\n|align=left|[[Gordon Strachan|Strachan]] (54 [[Penalty kick (association football)|pen.]]), [[Neil Simpson|Simpson]] (58), [[Mark McGhee|McGhee]] (86)\n|29,733\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|7.\n|align=left|16 October\n|align=left|[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]\n|[[Pittodrie Stadium|H]]\n|1\u20130\n|align=left|[[Peter Weir (footballer)|Weir]] (34)\n|10,800\n|-bgcolor=#EEFFEE\n|8.\n|align=left|23 October\n|align=left|[[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]\n|[[Rugby Park|A]]\n|2\u20130\